    <section class="recipe">
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup butter</li>
            <li>1 cup white sugar</li>
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
            <li>1 1/2 cups chocolate chips</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).</li>
            <li>Mix butter and sugar until creamy.</li>
            <li>Add flour and vanilla extract. Stir until smooth.</li>
            <li>Fold in chocolate chips.</li>
            <li>Form dough into small balls and place on a baking sheet.</li>
            <li>Bake for 10-12 minutes until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Let cool, then enjoy your cookies!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

